problem_text: Yale University is a private Ivy League research university. Yale University moved to New Haven in 1716. Yale university's endowment was valued at $42.3 billion. Yale University has been organized into 27 constituent colleges and schools: the residential colleges, the Yale Graduate School of Arts and Sciences, and twelve professional schools. A list of residential colleges at Yale: Benjamin Franklin College, Berkeley College, Branford College, Davenport College, Ezra Stiles College, Grace Hopper College, Jonathan Edwards College, Morse College, Pauli Murray College, Pierson College, Saybrook College, Silliman College, Timothy Dwight College, and Trumbull College.
predicates:
University(x) ::: x is a university.
Private(x) ::: x is private.
IvyLeague(x) ::: x is an Ivy League university.
Research(x) ::: x is a research university.
Location(x, y) ::: x is located in y.
Year(x) ::: x is a year.
EndowmentValue(x, y) ::: x has an endowment valued at y.
Organized(x, y) ::: x is organized into y constituent colleges and schools.
College(x) ::: x is a constituent college or school.
Name(x, y) ::: x is named y.

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? There exists a constituent college of Yale University that is not named Benjamin Franklin College.
tests.conclusions: ∃x (College(x) ∧ Location(x, newHaven) ∧ Name(x, benjaminFranklinCollege)) ::: There exists a constituent college of Yale University named Benjamin Franklin College that is located in New Haven. FALSE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Yale University is a research university and has an endowment valued at $42.3 billion.
tests.conclusions: Research(yale) ∧ EndowmentValue(yale, 42.3billion) ::: Yale University is a research university and has an endowment valued at $42.3 billion. TRUE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Yale University was organized into 27 constituent colleges and schools and was located in New Haven in 1716.
tests.conclusions: ∀x (University(yale) ∧ Organized(yale, 27) ∧ Location(yale, newhaven) ∧ Year(year1716)) ::: Yale University was organized into 27 constituent colleges and schools and was located in New Haven in 1716. FALSE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Benjamin Franklin College is a constituent college of Yale University and Yale University is a private university.
tests.conclusions: College(benjaminFranklinCollege) ∧ Private(yaleUniversity) ::: Benjamin Franklin College is a constituent college of Yale University and Yale University is a private university. TRUE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Yale University is an Ivy League university and is named Benjamin Franklin College.
tests.conclusions: IvyLeague(yale) ∧ Name(yale, benjaminFranklinCollege) ::: Yale University is an Ivy League university and is named Benjamin Franklin College. FALSE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Yale University is a research university and has an endowment valued at $42.3 billion, and was organized into 27 constituent colleges and schools.
tests.conclusions: Research(yale) ∧ EndowmentValue(yale, 42.3billion) ∧ Organized(yale, 27) ::: Yale University is a research university and has an endowment valued at $42.3 billion, and was organized into 27 constituent colleges and schools. TRUE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Yale University is a private university and is organized into 27 constituent colleges and schools, and it is not true that all constituent colleges are private.
tests.conclusions: University(yale) ∧ Private(yale) ∧ Organized(yale, 27) ∧ ¬∀x(College(x) ∧ Location(x, newhaven) → Private(x)) ::: FALSE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Yale University is a private university and is named "Yale University", or Yale University is not a private university and is not named "Yale University".

Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Yale University is a research university that was organized into 27 constituent colleges and schools, and Benjamin Franklin College is a constituent college of Yale University and is named Benjamin Franklin College.
tests.conclusions: Research(yale) ∧ Organized(yale, 27) ∧ (College(benjaminFranklinCollege) ∧ Name(benjaminFranklinCollege, "Benjamin Franklin College")) ::: TRUE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Yale University is a private university and was organized into 27 constituent colleges and schools, and Benjamin Franklin College is a constituent college of Yale University and is named Benjamin Franklin College.
tests.conclusions: Private(yale) ∧ ∃x (Organized(yale, x) ∧ College(x)) ∧ ∃x (College(x) ∧ Name(x, benjaminfranklin) ∧ Location(benjaminfranklin, yale)) ::: TRUE
